New Orleans Saints linebacker
Jonathan Vilma sued National Football League Commissioner  Roger
Goodell  for defamation in federal court in New Orleans.  Vilma accused the commissioner of making false statements
about him in reports discussing the Saints’ alleged “bounty”
program.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Dunn in New York at 
